    "last_activity_date" : 1560853497,
    "creation_date" : 1560853497,
    "answer_id" : 56646995,
    "question_id" : 10332132,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just consider how the SWITCH might work, </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>in case of primitives we know it can fail with NPE for auto-boxing</li>\n<li>but for <strong>String</strong> or <strong>enum</strong>, it might be invoking equals method, which obviously needs a LHS value on which equals is being invoked.\nSo, given no method can be invoked on a null, <em>switch</em> cant handle null.</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
